fields.description: The hot water system delivers heated water to guest rooms, kitchens, and staff facilities for bathing, cleaning, and operational use. The system consists of water heaters (electric or gas), circulation pumps, mixing valves, and insulated piping. It is designed to maintain consistent water temperature and availability, while minimizing energy consumption and ensuring guest comfort. Regular checks are carried out to monitor temperature settings, detect faults, and prevent scalding or system failure.
